TODO: Docker commands to spin up MongoDB and microservice containers
Run commands for respective microservices inside corresponding project root directories


For MongoDB container:

1. docker run -d -p 27017:27017 --name mongodb1 mongo


For Eureka Service Discovery:

1. docker build -t servicediscovery/eureka .
2. docker run -id -P 8761:8761 --name eureka servicediscovery/eureka


For employee microservice:

1. docker build -t microservice/employee .
2. docker run -d -P --link mongodb1 --link eureka --name employee microservice/employee

For mission microservice:

1. docker build -t microservice/mission .
2. docker run -d -P --link mongodb1 --link eureka --name mission microservice/mission

For reward microservice:

1. docker build -t microservice/reward .
2. docker run -d -P --link mongodb1 --link eureka --name reward microservice/reward

To view all running containers with exposed ports and ports on host on which the services are accessible:

docker ps
